{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nWire the code_health metric specs to read via the analyzer (LOC/complexity/duplication) instead of scanning `src/rebar/**/*.py` and `.github/module-size-limit.txt`. Re-express the module-size cap as an OPTIONAL policy over the analyzer LOC signal (from the `[code_health]` config), and make missing/unconfigured analyzer render honest Unavailable — killing the fabricated-zeros mode. Does NOT touch the CI module-size GATE (separate governance).\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- BOTH limit-file readers must be migrated: `module_size_distribution` AND `cap_change_events` read `.github/module-size-limit.txt` (git_metrics.py:167-229, registered ~:272) — remove/re-express both.\n- `module_size_trend` / `oversized_module_count` are currently SEED stubs (compute=_no_data_yet -> None); this ticket WIRES them to the analyzer (they read nothing today).\n- Cap value comes from the `[code_health]` config section created in e7a0 (recorded dep via the adapter chain); consuming that config is THIS tickets job.\n- `analyzer.py` is created by 3b30 — reference, do not re-create.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] module_size_distribution, oversized_module_count, module_size_trend, AND cap_change_events read via the analyzer / config; no `src/rebar` or `.github/module-size-limit.txt` reference remains in the metric readers.\n- [ ] Module-size cap sourced from `[code_health]` config as an optional policy over the LOC signal (not hardcoded).\n- [ ] No analyzer configured -> Unavailable; regression test asserts NO `{count:0,max_loc:0}` authoritative value and NO leaked errno reason.\n- [ ] git-delta (churn/refactor_ratio) + agent_process metrics unchanged.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Regression test (foreign repo -> honest Unavailable, not fabricated zeros); full in-repo `rebar metrics` green for unaffected metrics.\n\n## Dependencies: 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0 (adapters). Recorded edges: depends_on 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0.\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py, src/rebar/metrics/registry.py, src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py (consume), tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py\n## Estimated scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784523341428266001,"uuid":"ec0b2898-877a-493e-8e6f-3824447f6858"}